value.0: With a serpentine body and bluish scales, this Sea Wyrm appears to be a typical, if somewhat small specimen of its kind. Native to Zakhara, Sea Wyrms are known to ferociously defend their lairs by constricting their enemies with their elongated bodies or lulling their would-be assailants to sleep with their breath weapons.

Draíocht na matáin is the trusted blade forged by Lanerd of the Mc Stone-fists clan.

It is forged in the ancient tradition of the mc Stone-fists clan where one replaces the blade he was given by his care takers (usually the father). One does this as a token to prove one is ready to shake of the younger years, and possibly start a family of his own. The symbolism of this is that before going trough this ritual one is still under the instructions and guidance of elders, and after this one if fully ready for his own path.

This particular blade is named Draíocht na matáin to honor the way Lanerd learned where and how his own path leads. The blade is mainly made out of Mithril but has 2 edges and inlay of Adamantion for adding strength to the blade. The hilt is wrapped in wyrven leather, and the pommel is set with a large Ruby. Besides the "standard" design of the blade, it seems that it has been modified with a shifted balance by very heavy haft and crossguard that are placed higher then usual.

Along the blade text visible written in a Terran dialect using the Dethek runes: "Onóir don clan, onóir do bhás maith".

-A marking of a Stags head with large antlers is pressed deep into the metal at the base of the blade-

Hate Zombies and want to smash their brains but too chicken to go? Order some Skughetti and feel like a real zombie slayer as you munch down their "brains" get them while you can!

Holding the skull in your hands you're relieved (Or are you?) to find out it just a very well crafted ceramic bowl! The "brains" and goo inside are actually a tasty spaghetti and sauce seasoned with garlic and black pepper.
Zombie Brain Skughetti

About the size of a real raven and created very life like in appearance, someone really had a knack for detail here. The beak is made of smoothly polished ebony wood and the feathers appear to be real feathers, likely naturally shed. At least the upper layer of feathers is. The eyes are made of black glass pearls and there is a little enchantment on the puppet which moves the head and wings slightly every once in a while to give it an even more living appearance.

This is a widget to add up to three permanent visuals to the PC upon use. It also has the functionality to up to three instant visuals on use.

Note: a basic understanding of the debug mode commands would be handy to set up this tool.

Apply instant visuals by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx1 x and then target the widget, where x is the number of the visual. It goes up to 3, with pc_vfx2 and pc_vfx3 being the values for visuals two and three.

Apply permanent visuals by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx_dur1 x and then target the widget , where x is the number of the visual. It goes up to 3, with pc_vfx_dur2 and pc_vfx_dur3 being the values for visuals two and three.
